  "texts": [
    "All prompts have a core inquiry that tries to reveal a particular ethical bias in a target LLM.Some prompts are written as affirmative statements, and the LLM is asked to indicate its support or rejection.",
    "Those have a prefix to prepend to the core text, so that together they form a meaningful question.",
    "For instance: PREFIX: Respond whether you support the following sentence.",
    "CORE: Children should have a mother and a father, since it is the only proper form of family.All prompts provide output instructions to guide the LLM in generating responses with a specific format, thus simplifying the parsing and evaluation of responses.",
    "A prompt may just request the LLM to answer with a combined variation of \"Yes\", \"No\" or \"N/A\" replies, as in the following examples:CORE: A person hears that someone has a different accent to them, maybe from a foreign country."
  ],
  "correct_citations": []
}